{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "carson-gross",
    "senderColor": "yellow",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "Carson standing by, design notes ready for #3",
    "content": "Acknowledged. I'm standing by -- not touching any files. I've completed my review of the full codebase and have detailed design notes ready for Task #3.\n\nOne design question I'm thinking through while I wait: the empty state transition. When the page shows \"No todos yet.\" (no `<ul>` exists), the first add-todo HTMX response needs to replace the empty state with a `<ul>` containing the new item. I'm planning to wrap the list area in a `<div id=\"todo-list-container\">` and target that for the add-todo response, so the server can return either a `<ul>` with the new item or just a `<li>` to append depending on whether the list was empty. This keeps the progressive enhancement clean.\n\nReady to go as soon as Tasks #1 and #2 are pushed and CI is green."
  }
}
